claim.claim-text:
1. A method of coupling an ancillary instrument to an orthopedic instrument comprising the steps of:
providing a coupler having a first portion having a first axis, a second portion having a second axis rotatably mounted relative to the first portion, and a trigger fixed to the second portion wherein the trigger is biased to a first position in which the first and second portions are misaligned such that the axes are askew and can be actuated to a second position in which the first and second portions are aligned such that the axes are coaxial;
coupling the coupler to the ancillary instrument;
actuating the trigger to the second position;
inserting at least portions of the first and second portions in an aperture of the orthopedic instrument; and
releasing the trigger.

13. A method of coupling an ancillary instrument to an orthopedic instrument comprising the steps of:
providing a coupler having a first portion having a first axis, a second portion having a second axis rotatably mounted relative to the first portion, and a trigger fixed to the second portion wherein the trigger is biased by a spring to a first position in which the first and second portions are misaligned such that the axes are askew and can be actuated to a second position in which the first and second portions are aligned such that the axes are coaxial;
coupling the coupler to the ancillary instrument;
actuating the trigger to the second position;
inserting at least portions of the first and second portions in an aperture of the orthopedic instrument; and
releasing the trigger,
wherein the actuation step includes moving the trigger in a first direction and the inserting step includes moving the coupler in a second direction, the first and second directions being perpendicular.

23. A method of coupling an ancillary instrument to an orthopedic instrument comprising the steps of:
providing a coupler having a first portion having a first axis, a second portion having a second axis rotatably mounted relative to the first portion, and a trigger fixed to the second portion wherein the trigger is biased to a first position in which the first and second portions are misaligned such that the axes are askew and can be actuated to a second position in which the first and second portions are aligned such that the axes are coaxial;
coupling the coupler to the ancillary instrument;
actuating the trigger to the second position;
inserting at least portions of the first and second portions in an aperture of the orthopedic instrument;
engaging a locking element of the coupler with a corresponding aperture of the orthopedic instrument; and
releasing the trigger.
